            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "Yeah, I agree.\n\nMy use case for this idea is that I want to run the last shell command and go back to current file quickly, like this\n\n```\n<C-w>l     \" to the terminal, supposedly enter insert mode automatically\n<C-p><enter> \" run previous command\n<C-w>r    \" back to the file. I mapped it to <C-\\><C-n><C-w>r\n```\n\nThe key point is simply that holding Ctrl throughout the steps is smoother. \n\nIs there a good way to  run the last command while still in the Normal mode?\n",
