            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "To enter insert mode every time you enter a terminal buffer, put this in your vimrc:\n\n``` vim\nautocmd BufEnter term://* startinsert\n```\n\nThis little script shows how to send lines to a terminal buffer as commands and remember the last command:\n\n``` vim\nlet s:last_cmd = ''\nlet s:term = termopen([&shell])\n\nfunction s:send(cmd)\n  let s:last_cmd = a:cmd . \"\\n\"\n  call jobsend(s:term, s:last_cmd)\nendfunction\n\nfunction s:repeat()\n  call jobsend(s:term, s:last_cmd)\nendfunction\n\ncommand -nargs=+ Send call s:send(<q-args>)\ncommand -nargs=0 Repeat call s:repeat()\n```\n\nnvim itself doesn't keep any tabs on what you send to the buffer and can't tell the difference between that and program output, so such a thing can't be a built-in feature right now.\n",
